<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#123#000036#       114#">Va. Code Ann. § 36-114</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_36-114"/><heading><desig>§ 36-114.</desig><title>Board to hear appeals</title></heading><bodyText><p>The Review Board shall have the power and duty to hear all appeals from decisions arising under application of the Building Code, the Virginia Amusement Device Regulations adopted pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 36-98.3"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 36 -98.3">§ 36-98.3<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000036#      98.3#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, the Fire Prevention Code adopted under the Statewide Fire Prevention Code Act (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 27-94"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 27 -94">§ 27-94<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#123#000027#        94#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.), and rules and regulations implementing the Industrialized Building Safety Law (§ 36-70 et seq.), and to render its decision on any such appeal, which decision shall be final if no appeal is made therefrom. Proceedings of the Review Board shall be governed by the provisions of the Administrative Process Act (<citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4000"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4000">§ 2.2-4000<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4000#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> et seq.), except that an informal conference pursuant to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4019"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4019">§ 2.2-4019<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4019#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> shall not be required.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1972, c. 829; 1977, c. 423; 1986, cc. 37, 429; <citation normalizedCite="1994 VA CH 406"><content><span normalizedCite="1994 Va. Ch. 406">1994, c. 406<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1994#000406#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2003 VA CH 650"><content><span normalizedCite="2003 Va. Ch. 650">2003, c. 650<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2003#000650#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2010 VA CH 63"><content><span normalizedCite="2010 Va. Ch. 63">2010, c. 63<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2010#000063#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PT30-004G-K3YY-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All right